article.headline: Oakland 74, Wisconsin-Green Bay 57
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. (AP) -- Vova Severovas had 22 points and nine rebounds to lead Oakland to a 74-57 victory over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Sunday. Severovas scored 13 of his 22 points in the second half for the Golden Grizzlies (2-0), who opened the game with an 18-2 run and never trailed. Severovas finished 14-of-15 from the free-throw line. Ryan Tillema sank a pair of free throws to help the Phoenix (0-1) pull within 15 points with two minutes left to play. But Oakland grabbed key defensive rebounds down the stretch to defuse the rally. Ryan Evanochko led Green Bay with 21 points, six rebounds and three steals. Tillema finished with 14 points. Erik Kangas hit 4-of-7 from 3-point range and finished with 20 points for the Grizzlies. Rick Billings added 12 points and six rebounds.
